<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00116</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING A HOSPITAL FOR TEACHERS AND THEIR DEPENDENTS, APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Establishes a hospital for teachers which shall be the primary medical facility for the hospitalization and medical care of teachers and their dependents.

Mandates each regional hospital to establish a teachers’ ward with an initial capacity of at least fifty (50) beds which will provides hospital and medical care to teachers and their dependents residing outside of the National Capital Region.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Philippine Teacher’ Hospital Act of 2016.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>MACAPAGAL ARROYO, JUAN MIGUEL</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Madrona (000 2019-08-01)</td><td>2. Olivarez (000 2019-08-29)</td><tr><td>3. Sy-Alvarado (000 2019-10-01)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2019-07-23</td></tr></table>